{"id": "c6h9do", "title": "Dr. Stranglelove, or: How I Learned to Stop YOLOing Options and Lovin 2 Bomb", "selftext": "1. If you think you have a better spread than a simple straddle or strangle, and have less than $10k to burn, don't sell premiums you can't cover as part of an options strategy. Better autists before you have done all-star DD and still ended up negative 5 figures that way.  \n\n2. Never buy an option contract simply because you can afford it. This makes you a garbage person. Garbage people take burdensome leftovers that strangers want gone once a week  \n\n3. Options calculator. Watching folks buy options confidently based on op interest/volume alone was a fun for a while, but if more WSBers used   [https://www.optionsprofitcalculator.com](https://www.optionsprofitcalculator.com/) we wouldn't need crisis hotline bot as much  \n\n4. I now tend to only average down my losses when those losses are caused by temporary news (and if I have enough day trades to cut further losses if needed) .   \n\n5. For fucks sake. Lay off the round trips for a week, actually give yourself a morsel of a chance.  \n\n\nI'm not an emotional trader, but I did catch myself caught up in stupid PDT OCD this past month. Knew I needed to do some DD on myself.  \n\n\nThose are a few ways in which I've noticed loss patterns accruing during rainbow markets. Might add more in comments.", "created_utc": 1561706937, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/c6h9do/dr_stranglelove_or_how_i_learned_to_stop_yoloing/", "is_self": true}